thread.title: Omaha Weather: Windy & warmer Friday

author: @WOWT6News
title: Omaha Weather: Windy & warmer Friday
text:
Boâ€™s First Alert 6 Forecast: Winds calm down briefly tonight, strong winds return Friday
OMAHA, Neb. (WOWT) - The winds did not disappoint as numerous communities saw winds gusting up to 50-55 mph! OPPD even reported near 1,000 customers are without power as of 3:30 Thursday afternoon.
Winds will continue to be strong from the northwest gusting up to 50-55 mph until midnight. After midnight, winds will calm down drastically but it will only be brief.
Temperature will continue to be cold with lows falling to the mid teens. Wind chills will be in the single digits with some communities falling to below zero.
South wind gusts will pick up on Friday and help us rebound significantly into the afternoon. Highs in the mid 40s are likely as gusts hit 30-40 mph at times.
The weather will be much calmer into the weekend though with mild highs in the 40s.
The week leading up to Christmas will be very mild with highs in the 50s including Christmas. No white Christmas this year.
The record high of 57 degrees is within reach as well.
